descript.abstract: This dataset depicts the Yolo and Sutter bypass areas designated as Critical Habitat for the Southern Distinct Population Segment (DPS) of Green Sturgeon.
descript.purpose: This dataset was developed to show those areasof the Yolo and Sutter bypasses designated as Green Sturgeon Critical Habitat. The data DO NOT constitute a legal description of critical habitat (which can be found in the agency's Federal Register notice describing the critical habitat designation - see 74 FR 52300, October 9, 2009).
descript.supplinf:
This dataset was created by modifying the existing Yolo and Sutter Bypass GIS boundaries according to where members of the NMFS critical habitat review team determined Green Sturgeon to be present.
This GIS file should be used in conjunction with the other Green Sturgeon Critical Habitat GIS files showing Estuaries, Marsh Areas, Marine Coastal Zones, Streams, Department of Defense Exclusions and Tribal Exclusions.

idinfo.accconst: To ensure an individual or an agency is using the most current and accurate representation of the Green Sturgeon Critical Habitat Designation GIS data, a request should be made directly to the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA), National Marine Fisheries Service (NMFS), South or Northwest Regions
idinfo.useconst: The purpose of this data set is to provide a general basemap for the location of marine areas designated as Endangered Species Act (ESA) critical habitat for the threatened Southern Distinct Population Segment of North American Green Sturgeon. The data DO NOT constitute a legal description of critical habitat (which can be found in the agency's Federal Register notice describing the designation - 74 FR 52300, October 9, 2009).
